The paper deals with the problem of detecting adversarial examples in image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed technique is based on image inpainting, which is a technique used in computer graphics and image processing (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the limitations of existing adversarial attacks and the need for better defenses, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach that combines different techniques to achieve better results, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
